  "prompt": "Are Kodak cameras still around?",
  "response": "Yes, Kodak cameras are still around, although the company has gone through significant changes over the years. Originally known for its film and cameras, Kodak filed for bankruptcy in 2012 and has since shifted its focus to other areas such as digital printing, packaging, and advanced materials. \n\nHowever, Kodak still produces some cameras, mainly targeted at the budget and entry-level market. These include digital point-and-shoot cameras and disposable film cameras. Additionally, Kodak licenses its brand to other companies that produce cameras and photography-related products. \n\nSo while Kodak is not the dominant force in the camera market that it once was, the brand is still present and continues to offer various photography products.",
